main event: Two red, round objects were spotted in the sky over Independence, Missouri on July 11, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were described as being the size of an automobile tire, approaching from 360 degrees and disappearing at 20 degrees elevation.
The objects were traveling at a high speed and faded out of sight to the east.
The objects were observed after they had already begun to break up, suggesting they were part of a larger meteor.
Both civilian and military personnel reported seeing the objects.
The objects were tracked on radar, but no aircraft were found in the area.
photographs: No photographs present in the report
